comment_data.body:
Because `close_cb` runs after the pipe has already been closed, but the `conhost` requires us to call `ClosePseudoConsole` before closing the pipe. This ensures the pipe can fully drain and prevent `conhost` from waiting indefinitely. Here are the relevant stack and code from `conhost`:
```c
0, ntdll.dll!NtWaitForSingleObject+0x14
1, KernelBase.dll!WaitForSingleObjectEx+0x8e
2, conhost.exe!Microsoft::Console::Render::Renderer::TriggerTeardown+0x2b
3, conhost.exe!Microsoft::Console::Interactivity::ServiceLocator::RundownAndExit+0x21
4, conhost.exe!Microsoft::Console::VirtualTerminal::VtIo::_ShutdownIfNeeded+0x2e
5, conhost.exe!Microsoft::Console::VirtualTerminal::VtIo::CloseOutput+0x67
6, conhost.exe!Microsoft::Console::Render::VtEngine::_Flush+0xa6
```
```c
// Method Description:
// - Called when the host is about to die, to give the renderer one last chance
